Rand Maintains Gains, Bonds Advance as Central Bank Leaves Rates Unchanged

-- B y   R o b e r t   B r a n d
-- 
2011-07-21T13:23:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-21/rand-maintains-gains-bonds-advance-as-central-bank-leaves-rates-unchanged.html
South Africa ’s rand maintained gains
versus the dollar and bonds gained after the Reserve Bank left
its repo rate unchanged at 5.50 percent in Pretoria today.  The rand traded at 6.8142 per dollar as of 3:19 p.m. in
Johannesburg, a gain of 1 percent since yesterday’s close. The
13.5 percent bond due 2015 gained 5 cents to 121.50 rand,
driving the yield down two basis points, or 0.02 percentage
point, to 7.35 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
